## ğŸŸ fish alias example

```sh
alias -s fscode "fscode --editor='code -w' --create='new' --remove='del' --move='mov' --exchange='mv --exchange -iT'"
```

## ğŸª¶ Tips

- To use hard links, you can use `--inode` to display hard link information. Use `--cp='ln -snT'` to replace the cp operation.
- To use soft links, you can modify the `[args...]` column and set the ID to 0; fscode will then automatically use create_args to create them. If you need to force-create and overwrite, you must manually change `--create_args='ln -snTf'`. Currently, only the "create" function supports custom arguments. If the project gets 1000 stars â­, I will consider adding custom arguments for all operations.
- To use `sudo`, you can set `--cmd_prefix=sudo`, which will add this prefix to all commands.

